10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 804, as
12 amended by Section 28, Chapter 310, O.S.L. 2023 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
13 Section 804), is amended to read as follows:
14 Section 804. A. No person shall act as an instructor unless
15 such person applies for and obtains from Service Oklahoma a license
16 in the manner and form prescribed by Service Oklahoma.
17 B. Rules promulgated by Service Oklahoma, in conjunction with
18 the Department of Public Safety, shall state the requirements for an
19 instructor’s license, including requirements concerning moral
20 character, physical condition, knowledge of the courses of
21 instruction, motor vehicle laws and safety principles and practices,
22 previous personnel and employment records, and such other matters as
23 Service Oklahoma, in conjunction with the Department of Public
24 Safety, may prescribe for the protection of the public.
